$e2 = Matrix([[0],[1]]);

$Te1 = $A->column(1);
$Te2 = $A->column(2);

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
If \( T: {\mathbb R}^2 \rightarrow {\mathbb R}^2 \) is a linear transformation such that 
\[
T\left($e1\right) = $Te1, \ \ \
T\left($e2\right) = $Te2,
\]
then the standard matrix of \( T \) is 
$BR
$BR\( A= \) \{ $A->ans_array(10) \}
END_TEXT
